      • run

        public static <T> GepResult<T> run(Individual<T>[] population,
                                   FitnessEnvironment<T> fe,
                                   SelectionMethod sm,
                                   ReproductionEnvironment re,
                                   int maxNumGenerations,
                                   double targetFitness,
                                   double fitnessEpsilon)
        Runs Gene Expression Programming to find a solution to the problem defined by the given parameters.
        This function will modify and update the given population array per generation.
        Parameters:
        population - The initial population
        fe - The fitness environment used to assess the fitness of individuals
        sm - The selection method to select individuals from the current generation to be part of the next one
        re - The reproduction environment used to genetically modify individuals
        maxNumGenerations - The maximum number of generations
        targetFitness - The optimal value of the fitness function (set to positive infinity if not known)
        fitnessEpsilon - The error allowed when comparing the floating point targetFitness with the current best fitness
        Returns:
        The result of the GEP execution.

      • run

        public static <T> GepResult<T> run(Individual<T>[] population,
                                   FitnessEnvironment<T> fe,
                                   SelectionMethod sm,
                                   ReproductionEnvironment re,
                                   int maxNumGenerations,
                                   double targetFitness)
        Runs Gene Expression Programming to find a solution to the problem defined by the given parameters.
        This function will modify and update the given population array per generation.
        This function sets the allowed error to zero. It is therefore only recommended for integer fitness functions. In case of possible floating point values use the overloaded functions that takes an epsilon as last parameter.
        Parameters:
        population - The initial population
        fe - The fitness environment used to assess the fitness of individuals
        sm - The selection method to select individuals from the current generation to be part of the next one
        re - The reproduction environment used to genetically modify individuals
        maxNumGenerations - The maximum number of generations
        targetFitness - The optimal value of the fitness function (set to positive infinity if not known)
        Returns:
        The result of the GEP execution.
